# IT-Tools Project Rules

## MANDATORY: Read Context Engineering Prompt First

**Before making ANY changes to this codebase, you MUST read and understand the CONTEXT_ENGINEERING_PROMPT.md file.**

This is non-negotiable and applies to:
- Adding new tools
- Modifying existing features
- Updating documentation
- Making any code changes

## Key Requirements from Context Engineering Prompt

### 1. Tool Addition Checklist
When adding a new tool, you MUST:
- [ ] Create tool definition in `src/tools/index.ts`
- [ ] Implement Vue component following established patterns
- [ ] Add to appropriate category
- [ ] Add translations in ALL language files (`locales/*.yml`)
- [ ] Update `public/sitemap.xml` with new tool entry
- [ ] Update `dist/sitemap.xml` with new tool entry
- [ ] Update `public/llms.txt` with tool information
- [ ] Increment tool counts in `llms.txt`
- [ ] Update category counts in `llms.txt`

### 2. Architecture Patterns
- Use Vue 3 Composition API
- Follow TypeScript strict mode
- Use UnoCSS for styling
- Implement i18n for all user-facing text
- Follow existing component structure in `src/tools/`

### 3. SEO and Documentation Updates
Every new tool requires:
- Sitemap entry with proper priority (0.7 for tools)
- LLMs.txt documentation update
- Proper meta tags and descriptions
- Alphabetical ordering in sitemap

### 4. Code Style
- ESLint rules are enforced
- Use Prettier for formatting
- Match indentation of surrounding code
- Follow existing naming conventions

### 5. Common Patterns
- Use `c-card` for tool containers
- Use `c-input-text` for text inputs
- Use `c-button` for actions
- Implement copy-to-clipboard functionality
- Add proper error handling

## File Structure Understanding
- `src/tools/index.ts` - Tool registry (ALWAYS update when adding tools)
- `src/tools/[category]/[tool-name]/` - Tool implementation
- `locales/*.yml` - Translations (ALL must be updated)
- `public/sitemap.xml` - SEO sitemap (MUST update)
- `public/llms.txt` - AI documentation (MUST update)

